{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"alias":"adept-hedge-stain","description":"# Ticket-store concurrency hardening + corruption remediation (follow-ups to f193)\n\nPlaceholder epic for the deferred, larger-scope work uncovered by the joe-debug\ninvestigation of bug **saggy-pupil-plant / f193** (concurrent access corrupts the\nticket store). The two quick wins from that investigation shipped separately:\n**fix #1** (reconciler workflows use full-history + merge, not shallow + rebase —\nkills the `SNAPSHOT_INCONSISTENT` source) and **fix #3** (fsck exempts\nreducer-ignored event types from `ORPHAN_EVENT` — removes the false positives).\nThis epic tracks the three durable/architectural items intentionally NOT done in\nthat pass.\n\n## Context\n\nThe store is per-event write-once JSON files on the `tickets` git branch, reconciled\nacross clones (laptop + CI reconciler) by git. The confirmed defects:\n\n- **RC1 (fixed, #1):** the CI reconciler used shallow `--depth=1` fetch + `git rebase`,\n  which resurrected compaction-deleted source files → `SNAPSHOT_INCONSISTENT`.\n- **RC2a (fixed, #3):** compaction folds only `KNOWN_EVENT_TYPES`, but fsck flagged\n  any pre-snapshot event missing from `source_event_uuids` — a false-positive\n  `ORPHAN_EVENT` on `REVIEW_RESULT`/non-KNOWN types.\n- **RC2b (deferred, #4 below):** a concurrent write on a stale base gets an HLC\n  timestamp below a peer's snapshot horizon; a clean merge keeps it as a pre-snapshot\n  event that replay silently skips — genuine data loss (still surfaced by fsck: ~11\n  KNOWN-type `-EDIT.json` orphans remain in the live store).\n- **Design-invariant gap (deferred, #2 below):** `docs/concurrency.md` invariant I1\n  says compaction must RENAME folded files to `*.retired` (unions cleanly under git);\n  the code has always hard-`os.remove()`d them (`compact.py:142`). The `.retired`\n  safety net was never implemented.\n\n## Scope\n\n### #2 — Implement the documented `*.retired` rename in compaction (defense-in-depth)\nReplace compaction's hard `os.remove()` of folded source files with the rename-to\n-`*.retired` scheme the docs already specify (invariant I1), so that NO delete/add\nreconciliation (merge OR rebase, shallow OR full) can ever resurrect a source event.\nSpans `_commands/compact.py` (rename instead of delete), `reducer/_processors.py`\n(ignore `*.retired` on replay), and `_commands/fsck.py` (understand `*.retired`;\npossibly a reaper for old retired files). This is the durable class-fix that makes\nRC1-style corruption structurally impossible even if a workflow regresses.\n\n### #4 — Snapshot-horizon-safe compaction / merge reconciliation (RC2b)\nPrevent or absorb concurrent appends that land below a snapshot's horizon. Options to\nevaluate: a timestamp floor on the snapshot horizon; re-folding orphaned pre-snapshot\nevents on the next compaction; or a reconciliation step that detects a merged-in\npre-snapshot event and re-compacts. Must eliminate the silent replay-skip data-loss\npath (the replay rule at `reducer/_processors.py` skips events sorting before the\nlatest snapshot regardless of the source list).\n\n### #5 — Remediate the already-corrupted live store\nBuild a repair path (e.g. `fsck --repair`-style rebuild of snapshots from the event\nlog, or re-fold/re-compact from the full history) and run it to drive the existing\ninconsistencies to zero: ~2400 `SNAPSHOT_INCONSISTENT` + ~11 `ORPHAN_EVENT`\n(`-EDIT.json`) + 1 `MISSING_CREATE`. Must run only after #1 is deployed (so the\nreconciler stops re-introducing corruption) and coordinate with concurrent writers.\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n- Compaction is non-destructive (I1 `*.retired`) so delete/add reconciliation cannot\n  resurrect source events, verified by a two-clone merge+rebase test.\n- No concurrent sub-horizon append can be silently dropped on replay (#4), verified by\n  a two-clone regression test.\n- `rebar fsck` on the live store reports zero `SNAPSHOT_INCONSISTENT` / `ORPHAN_EVENT`\n  / `MISSING_CREATE` after remediation (#5).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Child story/task created for #2 (`*.retired` compaction) with a two-clone\n      merge+rebase resurrection regression test.\n- [ ] Child story/task created for #4 (snapshot-horizon-safe reconciliation) with a\n      two-clone sub-horizon-append data-loss regression test.\n- [ ] Child story/task created for #5 (store remediation tool + run) with before/after\n      fsck counts.\n- [ ] #5 is gated on #1 being deployed (reconciler no longer corrupting) — noted as a\n      dependency.\n- [ ] Each child follows RED→GREEN and lands via Gerrit.","id":"ace2-f784-4b19-4f22","parent_id":"","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"epic","title":"Ticket-store concurrency hardening + corruption remediation (follow-ups to f193)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783313480702574001,"uuid":"63e1d4ff-4e91-4013-8d27-bbd1548637e3"}